@endnode

@node ICONBOX_CONSTRUCTOR "iconbox_plugin: Constructors / Destructor"

   @{BG shine}Constructor@{BG back}

      @{b}iconbox(@{"tags" link ICONBOX_TAGS}=NIL:PTR TO tagitem)@{ub}

      For creating a new plugin object use for example:
      @{FG fill}
      DEF iconbox:PTR TO iconbox_plugin
      NEW iconbox.iconbox([..., TAG_DONE])
      @{FG text}

@endnode

@node ICONBOX_METHODS "iconbox_plugin: New Methods"

   @{b}set(@{"tag" link ICONBOX_TAGS}, value)@{ub}

      By calling this method it's possible to change attributes
      at runtime. You can use all tags with the S flag set.
      This method can also be used before the GUI is created and when
      the window is closed.
      Value is a LONG and contains the argument for the used tag.
      @{FG fill}
      Example:
      DEF iconbox:PTR TO iconbox_plugin
      ...
      NEW iconbox.iconbox([..., TAG_DONE])
      ...
      iconbox.set(PLA_IconBox_Disabled, TRUE)
      ...
      @{FG text}

   @{b}value,check:=get(@{"tag" link ICONBOX_TAGS})@{ub}

      This method is the counterpart to set. All tags with G flag
      can be used. Argument is the tag you want to get. Return values
      are the requested value and as second a boolean value. So if
      check is FALSE the used tag can't be get.

      @{FG fill}...
      value,check:=iconbox.get(PLA_IconBox_Disabled)
      ...@{FG text}

      After this:
       value=TRUE
       check=TRUE

@endnode

@node ICONBOX_TAGS "iconbox_plugin: Tags"
 The letters [ISG] show you when the tags can be used.
 I = @{"Initalisation" link ICONBOX_CONSTRUCTOR}
 S = @{"Set Method" link ICONBOX_METHODS}
 G = @{"Get Method" link ICONBOX_METHODS 18}


    @{FG shine}PLA_IconBox_IconName@{FG text}       [ISG]

        The name of the icon that should be displayed in
        the PLUGIN's area (do @{u}not@{uu} include the @{b}.info@{ub} part
        of the name).


    @{FG shine}PLA_IconBox_ShowSelected@{FG text}   [ISG]

        Boolean; whether or not to show the icon's
        selected image. Defaults to FALSE.


    @{FG shine}PLA_IconBox_Disabled@{FG text}       [ISG]

        Disable or enable the PLUGIN. Setting this tag causes the
        PLUGIN to become disabled; the area is ghosted.

        Boolean; defaults to FALSE.

@endnode

@node ICONBOX_EXCEPTIONS "iconbox_plugin: Exceptions"

   @{BG shine}Constructor@{BG back}

      "iblb" will be raised if the @{b}utility.library@{ub} or the
      @{b}icon.library@{ub} have not been opened.


@endnode

@node ICONBOX_HISTORY "iconbox_plugin: History"


    @{b}v1.0@{ub}                                   (30.8.97)

    o   Initial release.


    @{b}v1.1@{ub}                                   (2.10.97)

    o   Added some safety checks to ensure that the window
        is open before attempting to render into it in
        custom PLUGIN methods (set_disabled(), et al.)


    @{b}v1.2@{ub}                                   (28.10.97)

    o   Removed some unnecessary code from the render() method.


    @{b}v1.3@{ub}                                   (28.11.97)

    o   Removed the changing of icons by dropping (this is
        something that would be better handled in a user's
        @{b}awproc@{ub}).

    o   Rewritten to follow Ralph Wermke's PLUGIN Style Guide.
    

    @{b}v1.4@{ub}                                   (30.1.98)

    o   Bugfix: the appmessage method of the PLUGIN would
        only return true if the icon was dropped in the
        correct area and the PLUGIN was disabled. Of course,
        this should have been 'and the PLUGIN was @{b}not@{ub}
        disabled.' :)

    o   Documentation bugfix: @{b}PLA_IconBox_IconName@{ub} &
        @{b}PLA_IconBox_ShowSelected@{ub} are both @{FG shine}[ISG]@{FG text}, not
        just @{FG shine}[I..]@{FG text}.

@endnode
 

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       


